<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 4:12PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
west central Roanoke, east central Giles, southwestern Craig and
northeastern Montgomery Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 412 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Huffman, or near Newport, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sinking Creek...
Huffman...
Mc Donalds Mill...
Simmonsville...
and Bradshaw.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
